com.dd.plist

Class NSDictionary

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.dd.plist.NSObject
      • com.dd.plist.NSDictionary
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Map<String,NSObject>

    public class NSDictionary
extends NSObject
implements Map<String,NSObject>
    A NSDictionary is a collection of keys and values, essentially a Hashtable. The keys are simple Strings whereas the values can be any kind of NSObject.

    You can access the keys through the function allKeys(). Access to the objects stored for each key is given through the function objectoForKey(String key).

    Author:
    Daniel Dreibrodt
    See Also:
    Hashtable, NSObject
